1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a routing protocol for Wireless Body Area Sensor Networks (WBASNs) which involves designing energy efficient routing schemes for longevity of network lifetime. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper involves monitoring specific parameters of a soldier's body to measure fatigue, which can be considered as a human-computer interaction problem. 
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper involves monitoring soldiers for health purposes, which can be considered as a societal issue. 
4. cs.OH (Other Computer Science) - The paper involves a unique application of WBASNs for measuring fatigue of soldiers, which may not fit into any specific sub-category. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves designing a routing protocol for WBASNs, which can be considered as a systems and control problem.
